# Commit Message Conventions

## Overview

**MANDATORY**: When writing commit messages, follow this standardized format using conventional commits with emojis.

### Commit Message Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <emoji> <description>
[optional body]
[optional footer(s)]
```

### Types and Emojis

- feat: ✨ A new feature
- fix: 🔧 A bug fix
- docs: 📚 Documentation only changes
- style: 💎 Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
- refactor: ♻️ A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
- perf: ⚡ A code change that improves performance
- test: ✅ Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
- build: 📦 Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
- ci: ⚙️ Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
- chore: 🔨 Other changes that don't modify src or test files
- revert: ⏪ Reverts a previous commit

### Commit Message Rules

1. Use lowercase for type and description
2. Keep the description under 50 characters when possible
3. Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
4. Include scope when relevant (component, module, or area affected)
5. Always place the emoji after the colon, before the description
6. No period at the end of the description
7. Use body for additional context if needed (separate with blank line)
8. Never use `Made-with: Cursor` in commit messages
9. When attributing Cursor, use a Git trailer in footer format: `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
10. Keep at least one blank line between the commit body and trailer lines

### Cursor Co-Author Attribution

Use GitHub-compatible co-author trailers (per Git trailer format) instead of custom attribution text.

Correct:

```
feat(scope): ✨ add feature

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
```

Incorrect:

```
feat(scope): ✨ add feature

Made-with: Cursor
```

### Breaking Changes

For breaking changes, add `!` after the type/scope and include `BREAKING CHANGE:` in the footer.

### Examples

```
feat(auth): ✨ add user authentication system
fix(api): 🔧 resolve null pointer in response handler
docs(readme): 📚 update installation instructions
refactor(utils): ♻️ simplify date formatting logic
feat!: ✨ redesign user API

BREAKING CHANGE: user endpoint now returns different schema
```

This ensures consistent, descriptive commit messages that follow conventional commit standards while maintaining clear project history.
